<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>Memorandum by the Secretary of
                            State of a Conversation With President Truman</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1949v09</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d1440</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">1440</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1949-07-29T00:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1949-07-29T23:59:59-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-07-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-07-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="1440" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1440">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">026 China/7–2949</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                            State</gloss> of a Conversation With President <persName type="to">Truman</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-07-29">July 29,
                            1949</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Chinese White Paper</hi>
                </p>
                <p>I left with the President the memorandum on the China White Paper,<note n="45" xml:id="d1440fn45">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note> first of all going through with him the
                    various questions to ask whether he wished to decide them now or later.</p>
                <p>The President decided the White Paper would be released and it should be released
                    as soon as possible. He will be given a copy to read over the weekend. He and I
                    thought tentatively that probably the very last part of next week would be the
                    best time. Statements by him and <pb facs="1401" n="1391" xml:id="pg_1391"/> me
                    will be given to him on Monday, and he will tell us then the exact date, so that
                    we can go ahead with sending out copies, etc., etc.</p>
                <closer>[<signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dean Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>]</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
</TEI>
